#### Issue details
ZIndex usually change the "drawing order" of the actors and it should not effect the position of that actor within a layout managed group like HorizontalGroup. Trying to set Actor.toFront() which is a child of HorizontalGroup, will force the actor to be the last one in the list, the expect behavior that the Actor will be just drawing last and appear on top.  We need the layout help of the HorizontalGroup but to make extra effects that will go outside the actor/group bounds, we thought to use ZIndex / Actor.toFront() as currently anything drawing outside that bound is being hidden by neighbor actors.  The problem that the Group is using children array to manage drawing order, HorizontalGroup and other layout managed groups are using the same children array for the layout order too, I think they should be different arrays. 

