#### Issue details
The tile ID set by the [Tiled map editor](http://www.mapeditor.org/) does not correspond to the tile ID obtained with Libgdx. More precisely, they are mismatched by one. For instance, the tile with id 221 in Tiled becomes 222 in Libgdx.
```
 <tile id="221">
  <image width="128" height="128" source="tiles/ground.png"/>
 </tile>
```

#### Reproduction steps/code
Create a `test.tmx` map with a single tile (pay attention to its ID) and iterate over the tiles with the following code:
```
// Load the map
TiledMap map = new TmxMapLoader().load("test.tmx"); 
// Get the map size
int mapWidth = (Integer) this.map.getProperties().get("width");
int mapHeight = (Integer) this.map.getProperties().get("height");
// Iterate
for(int i=0; i<mapWidth; ++i) {
    for (int j = 0; j < mapHeight; ++j) {
        cell = layer.getCell(i, j);
        if (cell == null) continue;
        System.out.println(cell.getTile().getId());
    }
}
```
